Phase 2 -- osTicket via XAMPP

1. Stop IIS in the Services menu, set Manual on startup for World Wide Web Publishing Service
2. Download XAMPP & osTicket
3. Installed XAMPP
- Made sure Apache & MySQL were checked
4. Start Apache & MySQL
- MySQL started correctly, Apache would not start
- Found what was using port 80 in CMD, changed Apache config for port 8080 in XAMPP Control Panel
- HTTPS (port 443) was blocked as Apache was trying to start SSL on port 443, had to disable SSL in Apache
5. Create osTicket Database in MySQL
6. Extract and Place osTicket Files into C:\xampp\htdocs\
7. Configure osTicket
8. Fill in the osTicket Installer
9. Secure the Config File
10. Log Into osTicket Admin Panel
